    <title>Triple planes with p_g=q=0</title>
    <summary>  We show that general triple planes with p_g=q=0 belong to at most 12
families, that we call surfaces of type I,..., XII, and we prove that the
corresponding Tschirnhausen bundle is direct sum of two line bundles in cases
I, II, III, whereas is a rank 2 Steiner bundle in the remaining cases.
  We also provide existence results and explicit constructions for surfaces of
type I,..., VII, recovering all classical examples and discovering several new
ones. In particular, triple planes of type VII provide counterexamples to a
wrong claim made in 1942 by Bronowski.
</summary>
